MedicationOrderFact

The medication order fact contains information about medication orders. Each row represents an order.

For Epic data, this fact excludes historical orders and bulk dispense orders.

    FinalVerificationOutcome

    : string

    The final outcome during pharmacy verification of a new order. Shows if the order was verified or rejected. For Epic data, this column can return Verified, Rejected, Not Verified, Autoverified, Verified Before Release, Same User Released and Verified, or other values. This column returns Verified or Rejected for orders that populate the MinutesToManualFinalVerification column. If another value is returned, the value includes a description of why the order is not applicable to verification turnaround time. This column is not applicable for outpatient orders.
